01/06/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- The country assumed the rotating presidency of the Adriatic-Ionian Initiative on Sunday (June 1st). Foreign Ministry spokesman George Koumoutsakos announced on Thursday that Greece's priorities during its year at the helm will be to establish a permanent secretariat of the organisation and to promote co-operation against wildfires. Another focus will be to promote tourism by supporting small and medium-sized tourist enterprises. Initiative members include Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Slovenia, Serbia and Montenegro. (Naftemporiki - 01/06/08; ANA-MPA - 30/05/08)
